ed%20With%20Prison%20Time%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20Michigan%20couple%20has%20been%20arrested%20without%20bail%20in%20Mexico%20for%20allegedly%20scamming%20a%20hospitality%20company%2C%20prosecutors%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavy%20veteran%20Paul%20Akeo%2C%2058%2C%20and%20his%20wife%20Christy%2C%2060%2C%20were%20arrested%20on%20unresolved%20criminal%20fraud%20allegations%20when%20they%20were%20passing%20through%20customs%20on%20March%204%20following%20a%20financial%20dispute%20with%20The%20Palace%20Company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Akeo%20and%20Ms%20Christy%20left%20their%20home%20in%20Spring%20Arbour%20on%20March%204%20for%20the%20resort%20city%20of%20Cancun.%20Their%20family%20claimed%20they%20were%20stopped%20by%20police%20shortly%20after%20their%20plane%20touched%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDisputing%2013%20charges%20of%C2%A0approximately%20%24117%2C000%20on%20their%20credit%20cards%2C%20the%20couple%20is%20accused%20of%20scamming%20the%20holiday%20firm%20during%20their%20timeshare%20membership%20with%20its%20Cancun%20resort%20between%202021%20and%202022%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noindex%2Cnofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnypost.com%2F2025%2F03%2F28%2Fus-news%2Fmichigan-couple-in-mexican-prison-over-timeshare-fraud-charges-allegedly-encouraged-others-to-do-the-same-report%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pair%20allegedly%20advertised%20their%20accommodation%20for%20use%20on%20Facebook%20while%20they%20were%20not%20using%20it%2C%20and%20made%20%26quot%3Ba%20total%20of%201%2C570%20bookings%26quot%3B%20during%20their%20membership%2C%20which%20began%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20resort%20company%20claimed%C2%A0it%20terminated%20their%20benefits%20and%20planned%20stays%C2%A0after%20they%20%E2%80%9Cbreached%20their%20contract%20by%20promoting%E2%80%A6%20preferential%20rates%20and%20various%20benefits%20via%20social%20media.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20a%20Palace%20C