3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fjolts.nr0.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20offers%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20reduced%20competition%20for%20workers%20have%20weakened%20employees'%20bargaining%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLabor%20markets%20are%20still%20fairly%20strong%2C%20but%20nowhere%20near%20as%20tight%20as%20in%202022%2C%26quot%3B%20Harry%20Holzer%2C%20a%20nonresident%20senior%20fellow%20in%20economic%20studies%20at%20Brookings%20and%20a%20public%20policy%20professor%20at%20Georgetown%20University%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20really%20large%20gains%20in%202022%20were%20occurring%20during%20the%20Great%20Resignation%20when%20the%20labor%20market%20was%20extremely%20tight%2C%20and%20workers%20demanded%20higher%20pay%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20But%20now%2C%20%26quot%3Bquits%20have%20gone%20way%20down.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20shift%20is%20making%20many%20workers%20reluctant%20to%20leave%20their%20current%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCertainly%2C%20in%20DC%2C%20there's%20this%20feeling%20that%20you're%20better%20off%20staying%20put%20in%20a%20way%20right%20now%20with%20all%20the%20layoffs%2C%26quot%3B%20Elise%20Gould%2C%20a%20senior%20economist%20at%20the%20Economic%20Policy%20Institute%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20some%20economic%20insecurity%20that%20would%20be%20leading%20to%20this%20kind%20of%20phenomenon%20where%20people%20might%20be%20just%20staying%20still%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b6729c4b-f5a0-42d9-a778-dd2985ecd0b8%5C%22%3EThe%20wage%20squeeze%20in%20tech%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETech%20professionals%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20are%20feeling%20the%20effect%20of%20a%20cooling%20job%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJim%20Harrington%2C%20a%20principal%20software%20engineer%20at%20Cart.com%20who%20earns%20over%20%24200%2C000%20a%20year%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20during%20his%2012-month%20job%20search%2C%20he%20has%20seen%20wages%20on%20job%20listings%20top%20out%20at%20%24180%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20a%20bad%20wage%2C%20but%20it%20is%20not%20the%20levels%20that%20we%20were%20accustomed%20to%20seeing%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Levels.fyi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.levels.fyi%2F2024%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20wages%20for%20software%20engineers%2C%20product%20designers%2C%20and%20technical%20program%20managers%20fell%201-2%25%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20professionals%20have%20even%20left%20the%20industry%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERyan%20Essenburg%2C%20who%20said%20he%20worked%20for%2021%20years%20as%20a%20Business%20Development%20Director%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eat%20SimulTrans%2C%20a%20translation%20and%20localization%20services%20company%20in%20Mountain%20View%2C%20California%2C%20told%20BI%20he%20saw%20his%20position%20eliminated%20in%20April%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20what%20he%20termed%20an%20%26quot%3Bexistential%26quot%3B%20job%20search%20and%20lower%20salary%20offers%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20decided%20to%20put%20my%20search%20on%20indefinite%20hold%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20coaching%20tennis%20now%20and%20very%20happy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20have%20had%20to%20take%20significant%20pay%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERaymond%20Traylor%2C%20who%20was%20laid%20off%20as%20PairTree's%20Chief%20Technology%20Officer%20in%20December%202023%2C%20went%20from%20a%20%24180%2C000%20salary%20to%20%2436%2C000%20as%20a%20computer%20systems%20analyst%20at%20VSorts%2C%20a%20SaaS%20platform%2C%20from%20December%202023%20to%20March%202023%2C%20and%20has%20been%20earning%20between%20%243%2C000%20and%20%245%2C000%20a%20month%20as%20Negotiate%20Fairly's%20CTO%20and%20cofounder%20since%20March%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20been%20a%20multi-year%20downturn%2C%20but%20hopefully%20it's%20not%20too%20much%20longer%2C%20and%20I%20hope%20that%20we%20don't%20go%20back%20to%20just%20a%20boom-and-bust%20bubble%20sort%20of%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI%2C%20adding%20he%20hopes%20it's%20just%20an%20%26quot%3Bin-between%20weird%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225069edb2-18c1-4bf9-b639-f8262dcd5265%5C%22%3EWhat's%20next%20for%20wage%20growth%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20job%20stayers%20saw%20slightly%20higher%20pay%20raises%20than%20job%20switchers%20in%20February%2C%20their%20long-term%20prospects%20aren't%20much%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkplace%20advisory%20firm%20Willis%20Towers%20Watson%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wtwco.com%2Fen-us%2Fnews%2F2024%2F12%2Fus-salary-budgets-expected-to-remain-the-same-in-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprojects%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20US%20employees%20who%20stay%20in%20their%20roles%20will%20see%20an%20average%203.7%25%20salary%20increase%20in%202025%2C%20down%20from%203.8%25%20in%202024%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wtwco.com%2Fen-au%2Finsights%2F2023%2F01%2F2023-employee-pay-trends%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E4.6%25%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%202023%2C%20though%20still%20above%20the%20pre-pandemic%20norm%20of%203%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20economists%20warn%20this%20isn't%20just%20a%20temporary%20dip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20amount%20of%20uncertainty%20facing%20businesses%20today%20is%20leading%20to%20further%20reluctance%20to%20hire%2C%26quot%3B%20Thomas%20A.%20Kochanco%2C%20co-director%20of%20the%20MIT%20Institute%20for%20Work%20and%20Employment%20Research%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20anything%2C%20the%20labor%20market%20will%20get%20weaker%20in%20the%20months%20ahead.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20hope%20we%20are%20not%20in%20for%20a%20recession%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20that%20does%20occur%2C%20expect%20the%20bargaining%20power%20of%20both%20job%20hoppers%20and%20incumbents%20to%20continue%20to%20decline.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E